  <header class="guide-hero">
    <div class="kicker">Guide · Updated May 2026</div>
    <h1 itemprop="headline">Can Americans Travel to Cuba? Yes &mdash; Here&rsquo;s How (2026 Guide)</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Everything U.S. citizens need to know about legally traveling to Cuba in 2026:
      the 12 OFAC-authorized categories, required documents, direct flights,
      hotel rules, penalties for non-compliance, and step-by-step preparation.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div style="display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:16px; align-items:center; margin: -4px 0 20px; padding:10px 14px; background: var(--sr-gray-bg); border-left:3px solid var(--sr-blue); font-size:13px; color:var(--sr-gray-text);">
    <span><strong style="color:var(--sr-dark-text);">Last updated:</strong> May 13, 2026</span>
    <span><strong style="color:var(--sr-dark-text);">Sources:</strong> OFAC CACR (31 CFR Part 515), U.S. State Department, eCFR, Executive Order 14404</span>
  </div>

